The Chinese mainland recorded 415 new confirmed COVID-19 cases on Sunday, with 401 linked to local transmissions and 14 from overseas, data from the National Health Commission showed on Monday. A total of 3,918 new asymptomatic cases were also recorded on Sunday, and 92,564 asymptomatic patients remain under medical observation. Confirmed cases on the Chinese mainland now number 220,040, with the total death toll from COVID-19 at 5,185. The latest tally of confirmed cases in the Hong Kong and Macao special administrative regions and Taiwan region is as follows: Hong Kong: 331,274 (60,600 recoveries, 9,346 deaths) Macao: 82 (82 recoveries) Taiwan: 357,271 (13,742 recoveries, 919 deaths)